name: BrainSegNet
description: BrainSegNet is a PyTorch-based deep learning model for brain MRI segmentation using U-Net. It focuses on medical image analysis, enabling precise brain region segmentation for tasks like tumor detection. Includes data preprocessing, model training, and evaluation scripts.

name: Brain_tumor_detection
description: The repo presents the results of brain tumour detection  using various machine learning models. The dataset consists of 1500 tumour images and 1500 non-tumor images, making it a balanced dataset: Logistic Regression, SVC, k-Nearest Neighbors (kNN), Naive Bayes, Neural Networks,Random Forest,K-means clustering
